      "title": "Expand and simplify both sides",
      "content": "Left side: $$3(2x-8)-13 = 6x-24-13 = 6x-37$$<br/>Right side: $$4(x-4)+8 = 4x-16+8 = 4x-8$$<br/>Equation: $$6x-37 = 4x-8$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve for x and compute x-4",
      "content": "Subtract $4x$: $$2x-37 = -8$$<br/>Add $37$: $$2x = 29$$<br/>Divide by $2$: $$x = \\frac{29}{2}$$<br/>Compute $x-4$: $$x-4 = \\frac{29}{2} - 4 = \\frac{29}{2} - \\frac{8}{2} = \\frac{21}{2}$$<br/>That confirms <strong>B</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
